Jitters over the 2022 succession politics played out in the bicameral parliament as the two houses debated the unity pact between President Uhuru Kenyatta and opposition leader Raila Odinga. Allies of the deputy president came out to defend their leader against claims the pact may dim his star with Majority Leader Aden Duale clarifying that they were willing to negotiate with other parties on other positions other than that of flag bearer come 2022. The NASA wing on the other hand stating that the memorandum of understanding between the two party leaders was neither a merger nor a coalition but a meeting to put the interests of the country first. 